There's growing outrage on social media over a clip that went viral, of Limpopo Health MEC Phophi Ramathuba tell schoolgirls to quote,“ open your books and close your legs” and encouraged pupils to chant the slogan along with her. Ramathuba spoke with eNCA's Shahan Ramkissoon about her remarks. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Limpopo health MEC Phophi Ramathuba says her message addressed to school children is being taken out of context. The MEC bluntly told girls to "open their books and close their legs." READ: Sex Education to be intensified in schools She has been called out for putting the burden of sexual responsibility solely on girls. But the MEC says she has also advised the boy child not to engage in sexual activities. Limpopo health MEC Phophi Ramathuba says her message addressed to school children is being taken out of context. The MEC bluntly told girls to quote 'open their books and close their legs.' #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/yvQ9k0ZW1E